@Node "Introduction" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Introduction"

  @{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


    MUI.MiamiPanel is a MUI MiamiDx control panel.

    Miami-control-panel lets you control MiamiDx interfaces quickly.

    Holger wrote a brief documentation about panels in MiamiDx guide.

    MiamiDx panel api was written for ancient sixty years GUI systems,
    like the one in AmigaOS 3.5/9. It means that is not really usable
    with MUI.

    Usually, a MiamiDx panel is a simple window, that just asks MiamiDx
    to wait for some signals.

    This can't be applied to MUI. I didn't even tried.

    MUI.MiamiPanel runs as a stand alone process that comunicates
    with MiamiDx via Exec messages throght MiamiDx panel api.

    The result is quite ok. The speed is the same of plain.MiamiPanel,
    and the look is really better.

@EndNode

