@Node "Setup" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Setup"

  @{u}@{b}Setup@{ub}@{uu}


    First of all you must set MUI.MiamiPanel as the default panel:
    go to "MiamiDX/Gui/Control panel settings.../Panel module"
    and select "MUI.MiamiPanel".

    An interface will appear in the panel iff it is set to do
    that. In order to make an interface to be in the panel,
    go to "MiamiDx/Interfaces", doubleclick the interface and
    select the checkmark "Control panel".

    Some settings of the panel are available in
    "MiamiDx/GUI/Control panel settings..".
    There you may set:
    o Hotkey
    o Refresh time
    o Show on startup
    o Show transfer rate
    o Show total traffic
    o Show control gadgets
    o Show speed
    o Show online time
    o Show onl/off gadgets

    There are ignored:
    o Font (set it in MUI Settings)
    o Public screen (set it in MUI Settings)

    The MUI.MiamiPanel GUI is described @{"here" Link "GUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "GUI" "MUI.MiamiPanel - GUI"

  @{u}@{b}GUI@{ub}@{uu}


    MUI.MiamiPanel opens a very simple interface,
    whose main elements are:

    o @{"Menus             " Link "Menus"}
    o @{"Interface list    " Link "IFgroup"}
    o @{"Miami ctrls group " Link "CGroup"}
    o @{"Preferences window" Link "Prefs"}
    o About window


    ------------------------------------------------------
    Note that pressing the Help button in one of the above
    shows this guide.

@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Menus"

  @{u}@{b}Menus@{ub}@{uu}


    The MUI.MiamiPanel menus are:

    o Project

      - About
        Opens the About window

      - About MUI
        Opens the About MUI window

      - Hide
        The action taken depends on your @{"On iconify" Link "Prefs"} setting:
        If you choosed Quit, the panel is quit
        If you choosed Iconify, the panel is iconified

      - Quit
        Quit the panel


    o Miami (See @{"Miami ctrls group" Link "CGroup"})

      - Show
        Open Miami GUI

      - Hide
        Iconify Miami GUI

      - Quit
        Quit Miami


    o Preferences

      - Edit
        Open the @{"Preferences" Link "Prefs"} window

      - Save
        Save preferences to ENVARC:

      - Use
        Save preferences to ENV:

      - Restore
        Load preferences from ENV:

      - Last saveds
        Load preferences from ENVARC:

      - MUI Settings
        Open MUI Settings window

@EndNode

@Node "IFgroup" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Interfaces list"

  @{u}@{b}Interfaces list@{ub}@{uu}


    The interfaces list is a scrollable virtual
    group.

    If you choose to have the On/Offline gadget
    you will get one button for each interface.
    Pressing the button will put the interface
    On/Offline.

    The button contains a little lamp, the
    color of wich reflects the state of the
    interface and that may be adjusted in
    MUI/Lamp:

                Ok -> Online
               Off -> Offline
             Error -> Gonig online
           Warning -> Going offline
        FatalError -> Suspending
        Processing -> Suspended

    Any interface has also a ContextMenu that may be opened
    via the right mouse button. The menu items may be used
    to put an interface On/Offline.

@EndNode

@Node "CGroup" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Miami ctrls group"

  @{u}@{b}Miami ctrls group@{ub}@{uu}


    If you @{"choosed" Link "Setup"} to have the Miami ctrls, you
    will get a group made of 3 buttons. They may
    be used to control Miami:

    o Show
      Open Miami GUI

    o Hide
      Iconify Miami GUI

    o Quit
      Quit Miami

    See @{"Menus" Link "Menus"}.

@EndNode

@Node "Prefs" "MUI.MiamiPanel - Preferences"

  @{u}@{b}Preferences@{ub}@{uu}


    The Prefereces window lets you edit MUINL.MiamiPanel
    preferences.

      o Interfaces

        - Traffic format
          . Long
            The traffic is shown in bytes
          . Short
            The traffic is shown in Kb/Mb

        - Grouping
          If selected traffic digits are grouped

        - Rate format
          . Long
            The Rate is shown in bytes
          . Short
            The Rate is shown in Kb/Mb

        - Grouping
          If selected rate digits are grouped

        - Use busy bar
          If selected, a busy bar is used when an interface
          changes its state.

      o Miami ctrls

        - Position
          Let you choose where to put the Miami ctrls group

        - Framed
          If selected the Miami ctrls group is framed

        - Virt Frame
          If selected the Miami ctrls group uses the virtual frame
          If not selected the Miami ctrls group uses the group frame

        - Title
          If selected the Miami ctrls group is titled

      o Options

        - On iconify
          This may sound strange, but because of a MiamiPanel
          as no iconified state, you may decide to simply quit
          the panel when iconified, or to really iconify it.
          If iconified with an icon, the panel searches for
          ENVARC:Sys/MiamiPanel.info .

        - BWin
          If selected the panel will use BWin.mcc as window
          class. Note that a BWin.mcc window has a very
          usefull context menu.

      o Save
        Save preferences and exit

      o Use
        Use preferences and exit

      o Apply
        Apply preferences without saving, and exit

      o Test
        Test preferences without exiting

      o Cancel
        Exit without saving

    o Interfaces

      - Traffic

        . Format
          If set to Long the traffic is shown in bytes.
          If set to Short the traffic is shown in Kb/Mb.

        . No grouping
          If selected the traffic is not grouped.

      o Rate

        . Format
          If set to Long the rate is shown in bytes.
          If set to Short the rate is shown in Kb/Mb.

        . No grouping
          If selected the rate is not grouped.

      o Use busy bar
        If selected, yo will get a busy bar when an interface
        changes its state. The bad thing is that the interfaces
        flash a little bit when the bar is added/removed.


    - Miami (See @{"Miami ctrls group" Link "CGroup"})
      In this page you may adjust the appareance of the
      Miami ctrls group:

      o Position where to put Miami ctrls group

      o Framed if selected Miami ctrls group is framed


    - Options
      In this page you may adjust some global options:

      o On iconify (See @{"Menus" Link "Menus"})
        This may sound strange, but because of a MiamiPanel
        as no iconified state, you may decide to simply quit
        the panel when iconified, or to really iconify it.
        If iconified with an icon, the panel searches for
        ENVARC:Sys/MiamiPanel.info .

@EndNode

